!! Plugin Combiner

This plugin provides a widget to combine multiple TiddlyWiki plugins into a single plugin bundle.

!!! Features

* Select multiple plugins to combine
* Automatically resolves and includes plugin dependencies
* Configurable output plugin metadata (title, name, version, author, description)
* Downloads the combined plugin as a JSON file for import into other wikis

!!! Usage

The plugin adds a "Plugin Combiner" tab to the Control Panel where you can:

# Enter a plugin namespace prefix to filter the available plugins
# Configure the output plugin settings
# Select the plugins you want to combine
# Click "Download Combined Plugin" to download the bundled plugin

!!! Widget Attributes

The `<$plugin-combiner>` widget accepts the following attributes:

|!Attribute |!Description |!Default |
|`filter` |Filter to select which plugins to display |`[plugin-type[plugin]]` |
|`prefix` |Only show plugins with titles starting with this prefix |empty (show all) |
|`outputTitle` |Title for the combined plugin |`$:/plugins/custom/combined` |
|`outputName` |Display name for the combined plugin |`Combined Plugin` |
|`outputVersion` |Version string |`1.0.0` |
|`outputAuthor` |Author name |empty |
|`outputDescription` |Description text |`A combined plugin bundle` |
|`includeDependencies` |Whether to auto-include dependencies |`yes` |
